Third-party code redistributed in this repository
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

patches/
    The files under patches/ are unified diffs against Hermes-Agent
    (https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent), and therefore contain
    excerpts of Hermes-Agent source. Hermes-Agent is licensed under the MIT
    License, Copyright (c) NousResearch. Those excerpts remain under the MIT
    License; OKEngine's own patch logic is Apache-2.0. The MIT permission and
    copyright notice are preserved here as required by that license.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pinned dependencies (NOT vendored — cloned separately by the operator)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

OKEngine consumes, but does not redistribute, the following at the versions
pinned in engine-manifest.yaml:

  * Hermes-Agent — https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent (MIT)
        the agent runtime, cloned at a fixed tag; OKEngine layers an overlay
        plus the carried patches/ above. We do not fork it.
  * cron-plus (hermes-cron-plus) — https://github.com/jalewis/hermes-cron-plus
        the subprocess-per-job scheduler plugin, installed separately.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Generated content
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This repository ships NO domain knowledge and NO compiled vault content. A
deployment ingests the feeds the operator configures and compiles them into a
vault; that generated content is a derivative work of the ingested sources and
is the deploying operator's responsibility (respect each source's license and
any sensitivity marking). Domain packs live in the separate, public pack
catalog: https://github.com/jalewis/okpacks-library
